      "content": "The \"marketplace of ideas\" theory, championed by thinkers like John Stuart Mill, posits that truth emerges from the collision of all ideas, even false ones. Government moderation, however, inherently requires the state to act as a judge of truth, a role it is philosophically ill-equipped to perform. By censoring \"misinformation\" or \"hate speech,\" the government effectively decides which ideas are worthy of being heard, thereby corrupting the neutral, open exchange necessary for genuine intellectual progress.",
